@cnnphilippines 6,297 รท 7 = 899.5 per day. It's good.
Less 1k per day.

The new bulletin no longer indicates the number of recoveries and active cases, the positivity rate and the total number of infections. 

However, these can still be accessed in the website. https://t.co/487TjA42Me

The bulletin notes that 25.7% of ICU beds are occupied while 18.4% of non-ICU beds are in use. It also reports that 1,055 severe and critical cases are currently admitted in hospitals.

The DOH says 70.76% of the target population had been vaccinated.
The DOH earlier announced that beginning this week, it will only post COVID-19 case updates every Monday, including vaccination rates and healthcare utilization coverage.
